title: For Sale:  K-31 Schmidt-Rubin Swiss Rifle
postcontent:
This is quite a nice example of this rifle, it has a walnut stock with a noticeable tiger striping and is in overall great shape.  This rifle will likely outshoot your ability to aim it with the iron sights, you better have at least 20/20 vision if you expect to be its equal.  I have enjoyed shooting this rifle immensely, and you will too, the weight, wonderful two-stage trigger and overall design make for a very pleasant shooter.  The straight pull bolt is very unique and the machining in the cam mechanism is just a work of art, made by Sig in ~1939, it was issued to a citizen-soldier, and still has that previous Swiss owner's info card under the buttplate.  It also includes what appears to be an original leather sling with related hardware.  All serial numbers match on this rifle and blueing wear is quite minimal.

I also have ammo/brass for this rifle:
-2x 60rd packs of GP-11 surplus Swiss ammo, this is match grade stuff, really!   
-4x 20rd boxes of Prvi Partizan 174gr softpoint.  This is boxer primed, shoots quite well   and is suitable for hunting.
-140 rds of once-fired boxer-primed brass

$450 for the rifle and all ammo/brass and a nice long soft case that fits it well.

title: For Sale:  Tac Con Trigger (Simulates full Auto) for AR15
postcontent:
Check out the video

http://www.thebangswitch.com/tac-con-3mr-trigger/

I am dowtown Orlando during days and Oviedo, nights and eves.
I bought on locally while mine was on backorder, now I have one too many.

I am not a dealer. These list for $495, I am selling for $400,used for one outing and cleaned.

This is for the Trigger, Selector switch, ATF letter, box, the whole package ready to go.

See below:

3MR   trigger functions in a standard semi-auto mode with a 4.5lb trigger when the safety switch is in the standard Fire position. When you switch the selector switch back to where full auto would be on an M4/M16 you get the same 4.5lb semi-auto trigger, and the action of the bolt resets the trigger for you. All you have to worry about is pulling the trigger for the next shot.

The build quality is superb. USA manufactured utilizing CNC and EDM processes to produce the parts. The quality control process is top notch.

TAC-CON says the trigger is capable of a 600 rounds per minute (RPM) rate of fire. Most shooters will   be in the 400-500 RPM range,   Short travel distance and assisted reset means you have to do very little movement with your trigger hand.
Call text or email Rick 407-766-9048

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec 5.56 x 45 mm with many extras
postcontent: "Kel-Tec" is a gas-operated, semi-automatic pistol chambered in 5.56 NATO, manufactured by Kel-Tec Industries of Florida. The principal designer was George Kelgren, formerly of the the Intratec and Grendel firearms companies. The PLR (Pistol, Long Range) was designed for recreational target shooting, and small game, varmint, or predator hunting.[1] Due to the PLR’s relatively short barrel, the 5.56 cartridge’s velocity is considerably reduced compared to its velocity from a longer barrel. The PLR-16 combines the multi-lug rotating bolt design and breech-locking system of the AR-15 with a gas piston system similar to that of the M-1 Garand, M-14, and AK-47.[1] This system requires less maintenance than the direct gas impingement system of the AR-15 platform. The PLR-16’s frame is constructed of reinforced polymer, making the pistol both durable and light-weight. The frame incorporates an M-1913-style Picatinny rail molded to the top of the receiver to accept various optical sights.[1] Kel-Tec produces an optional polymer forend with a Picatinny rail for mounting flashlights or laser sights.This gun has it all! >>>  INCLUDES - LARGE RED DOT (8 BRIGHTNESS SETTINGS) SIGHT FOR QUICK ACQUISITION - 150 LUMEN PUSH BUTTON TACH LIGHT - GREEN PUSH BUTTON LASER (5mW) - SQUID FOREARM WITH RAIL - SLANT FOREGRIP (VERTICLE NOT LEGAL ON A PISTOL) - (1) 30 ROUND METAL MAG - (1) SUREFIRE 60 ROUND DOUBLE STACK METAL MAGAZINE - SOFT CASE W/ 4 MAG POUCHES - CENTER CARRY SLING - DOOR KNOCKER FLASH HIDER - 100 ROUNDS OF 5.56 X 45 AMMO. This beauty is a Model 32 or as it is commonly referred to as the “terrier”. It is not chambered for 38 special but rather 38 S&W cartridges. It is not as common as the Model 36 . Pistol was made between 1957 and 1961. S&W started marking the model numbers on their guns in 1957 and went to a “M 32-1” in 1961. So this pistol is over 50 years old.
Perhaps the best and most senior gunsmith in the area, Mr. Carl J. O'Connor, has inspected this weapon and certified that it is in "excellent condition."
